Jasmine Richards (born June 28, 1990) is a Canadian actress.

Biography

Richards is of French, Welsh, and Caribbean origin. She was born in Scarborough, Ontario, but moved to Oakville, Ontario when she was 1. She currently lives in Oakville, Ontario. Richards attended Iroquois Ridge High School. From 2005 to 2007, she co-starred as Margaret Browning-Levesque in the television series "Naturally, Sadie". Before that she co-starred in the 2005 film "Devotion" and the TV series "Timeblazers". She recently appeared as Margaret "Peggy" DuPree in the new Disney Channel Original Movie "Camp Rock". She was also the first and only Canadian to compete in the Disney Channel Games.

On September 24, 2008, Jasmine performed both American and Canadian anthems at the Rogers Center in Toronto, Ontario.

Personal Life

Richards is close friends with her Camp Rock castmates and 90210 star Shenae Grimes.
